Class that contains another way of representing orientation in 3D-space. Most game engines represent graphics with these values, because they are efficient at rotations.

Q0 = i axis (1st imaginary component) Q1 = j axis (2nd imaginary component) Q2 = k axis (3rd imaginary component) Q3 = s axis (Real component)

For more info visit: @link http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quaternion
